<Author>workandplay1
<Content>Hotel Policy For Memorial Day Weekend, I wanted to get away from home and decided to book a room at the Royal Villa. I went online and placed a reservation via their website. Nothing else happened, no follow up email or phone call, nothing. I thought that I had better follow up and call the hotel directly myself, but was told that they didn't have my reservation but do have rooms available so I proceeded to make a reservation. As I was giving the gentleman my information, he asked for my phone number. I gave it to him, he replied, do you live in Phoenix? I answered yes and he said that he could not allow me to stay there. I asked him why and all I was told is that the owners do not allow locals to stay at the hotel. But they do allow day passes to locals. I was totally confused and bewildered by this. I can understand that maybe in the past the hotel has had problems with locals, but give me a break. I will definately not recommend a place that can not even support its local gay community. 
